When my uncle died, his father said that the worst thing<br>
that can happen to a parent is that he survives past <br>
the death of his child. That is what Vietnam was about.<br>
For the U.S. and more so for the Vietnamese.<br><br>
What makes this even more upsetting is that it was done<br>
for the economic gain of a select few and did nothing<br>
to help or protect the average working american.<br><br>
May your generation learn that War should never be taken lightly<br>
and if you are ever in a position to consider if we should<br>
or should not go to war, remember that it could be your<br>
loved ones that come back in a body bag.<br><br>
P.S. Dont blame those who were sent to fight. They were not<br>
the cause of the problems or the benefactors of the war.<br><br>
WAR IS HELL !
